author: The Who
description:
[u'The Who (1964-1982) is an English rock band famous for songs like Pinball Wizard, My Generation and Behind Blue Eyes; however less known songs like I Don\'t Even Know Myself really speak to what the band was about. They were able to capture the change in culture between the 50\'s morals to 60\'s lack thereof; a time that left a whole generation unsure about where they fit in to the grander scheme of things. Their sound was also highly transitional. The band combined Rhythm and Blues with Rock, Pop and Punk into a sound that was unique to them.

They sold over 100 million records, released 27 hit singles and had 18 Gold Albums. The band was a major influence for artists like Led Zepplin and The Clash. In 1990, they were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame. Many consider them to be one of the best and most influential bands of all time.

Included in this collection are the following songs:
Behind Blue Eyes
Won\'t Get Fooled Again
I Don\'t Even Know Myself
My Generation
Overture
It\'s a Boy
1921
Amazing Journey
Sparks
The Hawker
Christmas
Cousin Kevin
The Acid Queen
Underture
Do You Think It\'s Alright?
Fiddle About
Pinball Wizard
There\'s a Doctor
Go to the Mirror
Tommy Can You Hear Me?
Smash the Mirror
Sensation
Miracle Cure
Sally Sampson
I\'m Free
Welcome
Tommy\'s Holiday Camp
We\'re Not Gonna Take It

Suggested Level: LS (Lower Secondary) OR US (Upper Secondary)
']

description:
[u'Bob Dylan is an American singer-songwriter who rose to prominence in the 1960s thanks to his folk songs (many of which have themes of social protest). \xa0He later reacted against the acoustic folk movement by "plugging in", employing electric guitar and a full band in his recordings. \xa0His influence on many key artists in rock music (examples include John Lennon, Patti Smith, and Bruce Springsteen) has earned him special awards from U.S. President Barack Obama and the Pulitzer Prize Committee, among others.

All of the songs included in this collection were written by Dylan.  Four of these recordings ("Blowin' in the Wind", "Masters of War", and "With God On Our Side") are performed by Dylan himself.  "A Hard Rain's A-Gonna Fall" is performed by Texas-based folk duo Carrie Elkin and Danny Schmidt, while "The Times They Are A-Changin'" is performed by contemporary roots-rock band Of A Revolution (better known as O.A.R.).

This collection includes a classroom activity related to the song "Blowin' in the Wind."']

author: Wilhelm, Hans
description:
[u'
Synopsis:\xa0Franklin\'s family lives in, well, a pigsty. As a meticulously neat piglet, Franklin finds his family\'s slovenly ways a great embarrassment, and he dares not encourage visitors. At school, his brothers\' unruly antics further humiliate him. All this changes when Franklin wins first prize for his painting of a rainbow. His father chooses the perfect spot to hang the picture, but Franklin asks him if he could first wash the wall. The entire family dives into a housecleaning spree and the result is a home worthy of Franklin\'s masterpiece. Friends even visit, and the family enjoys staying clean (except for an occasional mud bath). Wilhelm\'s book plunges right to the center of the concerns of children who sometimes feel like the odd member out among the people in their families. His text and watercolors capture the charms of this porcine clan both before and after their radical reformation. (From "Publishers Weekly").

(Franklin est le seul cochon propre de sa famille. Il n\'ose pas inviter ses amis chez lui. Apr\xe8s avoir peint un tr\xe8s beau dessin, sa famille d\xe9cide de se faire belle et de nettoyer la maison pour donner une place parfaite \xe0 ce dessin.)\xa0

Suggested level: EE, LP

']
subject: [u'Literature']
title: Quelle porcherie!
